{{draft}}
[[File:Kanasana-jinja_keidai.JPG|thumb|280x280px]]
{{Interlanguage link|Kanasana Jinja|ja|金鑚神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in Kodama County, Saitama Prefecture.<ref name=":1" /> It is a [[Ninomiya (shrine)|Ninomiya]], or a second rank shrine in its province after the [[Ichinomiya]], and is commonly called "NInomiya-sama"<ref name=":1" />

Every November 23rd it hosts a Hikiri Shinji, or "firestone festival"<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=Glossary of Shinto Names and Terms: K |url=https://www2.kokugakuin.ac.jp/ijcc/wp/glossary/def_K.html |access-date=2023-04-06 |website=www2.kokugakuin.ac.jp}}</ref>

== Architecture ==
It has a [[Gongen-zukuri]] style to its design<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Kanasana-jinja {{!}} Honjo Sightseeing Association |url=https://en.honjo-kanko.jp/sightseeing/kanasana-jinja.html |access-date=2023-04-06 |website=en.honjo-kanko.jp}}</ref>

It is generally built in a mixed architectural style<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kanasana jinja Shrine |url=https://www.guidoor.jp/en/places/5486 |access-date=2023-04-06 |website=Guidoor |language=en}}</ref>

It omits a [[Honden]] as the mountain behind it is its [[Shintai]].<ref name=":1" /> similar to [[Ōmiwa Shrine]]

It has a large [[camphor]] tree considered a national treature on its premies<ref name=":0" />

